node.text:

WOOD: Blond Limba
TEMPLATE: 3D Square Template
ROUTER BIT: @toolstoday 47222-S 
EPOXY: @squidpoxy Clear Fast
PIGMENT: @beaverdustpigments “Caribbean”, “Rainbow Blue” and “Dark Blue”
FINISH: @rubiomonocoatusa Pure 2C Oil 
-
Shop these supplies and more at www.JeffMackSupply.com
FREE SHIPPING to Canada and USA on orders over $300cad ($245usd)
-

node.text:
We just launched this honeycomb project kit on our website www.JeffMackSupply.com. It’s great for starters and can easily be made with different species or different epoxy colours.
-
Here’s what’s included:
1 piece of Yellow Heart
1 Honeycomb Template
1 Modern Handle Template
@squidpoxy Clear Fast 
20 @beaverdustpigments 
@walrusoil Cutting Board Oil
1 Pack of Wypall Shop Towels
-
Order now at www.JeffMackSupply.com
-

node.text:
Looking for an easy DIY Project!?
-
We now have these letter templates available so you can create your own custom monogram boards!
-
This video shows the steps we take to create a piece like this.
-
Here’s what we used:
Here's What We Used:
WOOD: Roasted Maple (from our 4"-8" wide listing)
EPOXY: @squidpoxy Clear Fast (perfect for small pours like this)
PIGMENT: @blackdiamondpigments_com "White Diamond Effect"
TEMPLATES: 1/4" Large Round and the Letter "S" (we have the whole alphabet available now)
TAPE: Painters Tape
TEMPLATE ADHESIVE: @akfixna 705 Universal Max Adhesive
ROUTER BIT: 3/16" flush trim router bit from @toolstoday 
FINISH: @rubiomonocoatusa Pure 2C Oil
-
Shop all these supplies and more at www.JeffMackSupply.com

node.text:
“What Finish Do We Use?” 
This is the most commonly asked question that we get asked. Here’s the answer and why we use it.
-
We use @rubiomonocoatusa Pure 2C Oil on every piece that leaves our shop! 
We love it because:
- it’s a great durable finish 
- it’s easy to apply
- it’s a one coat system
- zero VOC’s (safe to use)
- easy to refinish should you want to change the finish
- you can do spit repairs if the table gets a scratch or dent
- you can refresh it simply by using the “Refresh” or “Universal Maintenance Oil”
- you can achieve more sheen by sanding the finished piece and applying another coat
- you can buff it on or spread it with a squeegee
- it’s very reasonable priced when you factor in the coverage
- they offer tinted finishes so in one coat, you can change the entire look of the piece
We carry Rubio Monocoat is 6 different colours in 3 different sizes and we ship it to 66 countries.
Visit www.JeffMackSupply.com to shop now.
-
#RubioMonocoat #OilFinish #WoodWorking #Maker #Furniture #CustomFurniture

node.text:
Which board would you pick?! 
MOOSE OR SEA TURTLE?!?
-
One of our regular customers @wildwood.customwoodworking makes these beautiful boards using products from our online store. We have watched him grow over the years and we can’t wait to see what else he has up his sleeve. Go give him a follow! I promise you won’t be disappointed!
-
The Moose Serving Board was made using:
WOOD: Curly Roasted Maple
TEMPLATES: “Small Round Handle” and “Moose”
-
The Sea Turtle Serving Board was made using:
WOOD: Live Edge Cherry
TEMPLATE: “Sea Turtle”
-
Visit www.JeffMackSupply.com to shop wood, resin, pigments, templates, wood finish and more!
-
#Moose #SeaTurtle #ServingBoard #Maker #Charcuterie

TEMPLATE FAQ’s!!
You’re going to want to save this one!
-
Q: What router bit do you use?
A: We use a @toolstoday 47222-s flush trim bit. It has a 3/16” bearing so you can route all the details in our templates.
-
Q: What epoxy do you use:
A: we use @squidpoxy Clear Fast. Cures in 24 hours so you can finish your piece the next day.
-
Q: What pigment do you use?
A: We have been using @beaverdustpigments metallic pigments lately and love them. Full collection available VERY SOON!
-
Q: What sandpaper do you use?
A: We use @sia_abrasives_jjscanada 6” sand paper. We sand from 80 grit up to 220 or 320 before oiling.
-
Q: What finish do you use?
A: We use @walrusoil Cutting Board Oil.
-
Shop all these supplies and more at www.JeffMackSupply.com. We ship to 66 countries and we offer FREE SHIPPING TO CANADA AND USA on orders over $300cad ($245usd)
-

node.text:
#ThrowBackThursday!
Rob from @stonecitywoodworks challenged me to post a throwback photo from when I first started out. I couldn’t pick just one so I’ve got 10 for you guys to check out!
1) Brass Honeycomb + Walnut Coffee Table!
This was a collaboration with another woodworker and when he moved out west, he took and I never saw it again!
2) This was a project I worked on with an architect for a men’s clothing store in oakville @b.u.r.r.o.w.S 
3) We built this cabinet for @stemwinegroup in Vaughan along with many other pieces for their office! 
4) This display unit was custom built for @b.u.r.r.o.w.s to display smaller items in their store.
5) Custom built bench using reclaimed sassafras and steel legs with a high gloss clear finish for one of my very first and favourite customers. Pat and Wendy ❤️
6) Custom cnc cut privacy panels for an apartment lobby in Brampton.
7) Custom bench for my wife Laura. We still have it in our front hall!
8) we custom built tables, benches, countertops and signs for @tampcoffeeco in Burlington.
9) 48” by 48” custom coffee table for a local Toronto Client!
10) Custom TV stand for my wife. We still have this piece in our basement!
-
I nominate @wildwood.customwoodworking @makerwatchcompany and @northdogwoodco to share a few of their first pieces!
-
#WoodWorking #Maker #Wood #Mississauga #HandMade #WoodAndSteel #Toronto
